1. STEAM INSTALLER

SteamOS (Debian‑based)	
bash sudo apt update && sudo apt install steam

Fedora	
bash sudo dnf install steam
(REQUIREMENT TO ADD FIRST: 	Requires the RPM Fusion non‑free repository first:
bash sudo dnf install https://download1.rpmfusion.org/nonfree/fedora/rpmfusion-nonfree-release-$(rpm -E %fedora).noarch.rpm)

Common post‑install
bash steam (first launch will download additional runtime files)

2. UFW (Uncomplicated FireWall)

SteamOS
bash sudo apt install ufw
Enable with: sudo ufw enable.

Fedora	
bash sudo dnf install ufw

BASIC UFW RULE SET 	
bash sudo ufw default deny incoming
bash sudo ufw default allow outgoing
bash sudo ufw allow ssh
bash sudo ufw enable

3. NECESSARY DRIVERS

STEAMOS NVIDIA DRIVERS 
bash sudo apt update && sudo apt install nvidia-driver
restart

Fedora	
1. Enable RPM Fusion (both free & non‑free).
bash sudo dnf install https://download1.rpmfusion.org/free/fedora/rpmfusion-free-release-$(rpm -E %fedora).noarch.rpm
sudo dnf install https://download1.rpmfusion.org/nonfree/fedora/rpmfusion-nonfree-release-$(rpm -E %fedora).noarch.rpm
2. Install the driver:
bash sudo dnf install akmod-nvidia (pulls the latest stable driver).
3. Optional: sudo dnf install xorg-x11-drv-nvidia-cuda for CUDA support.
4. restart


Verification of successful install
bash nvidia-smi (shows driver version, GPU utilization).

